descript.abstract: U.S. and Canada City Points represents cities of the United States and Canada including national, state, and provincial capitals.
descript.purpose: U.S. and Canada City Points provides locations and attributes for the cities.
descript.supplinf: Largest scale when displaying the data: 1:100,000.

enttyp.enttypd: The points represent cities of the United States and Canada including national, state, and provincial capitals.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: The FIPS code (ten-digit number) for the state/province code, county code ("000" for Canada), and place code (Street Delivery Locality (SDL) for Canada).

codesetd.codesetn: Federal Information Processing Standards Pub 55; Abbreviations and Codes for Provinces and Territories
codesetd.codesets: National Institute of Standards and Technology; Statistics Canada

attr.attrdef: The state/province two-letter abbreviation for where the city is located.

codesetd.codesetn: Federal Information Processing Standards 5-2; Canadian Provinces and Territories
codesetd.codesets: National Institute of Standards and Technology; Canada Post Corporation

edom.edomvd: Population is between 100,000 and 299,999 in states/provinces where no cities are larger than 300,000

citeinfo.title: TomTom StreetMap Premium for ArcGIS - North America v. 11.1

procstep.procdesc: The following steps were performed by Esri: Extracted the dataset from TomTom StreetMap Premium for ArcGIS - North America v. 11.1. Created ArcGIS® layer file (.lyr), projection file (.prj), and spatial indices.

dataqual.logic: The shapefile is converted to SDC (Smart Data Compression) format using tools in ArcGIS. The SDC data set is then imported into a file geodatabase to verify, validate, and if needed repair the geometry.
dataqual.complete: After processing, the data set is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.

horizpa.horizpar: The horizontal positional accuracy is 167 feet.
